<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-09T00:00:00-00:44" n="569" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>On September 5, the Jordanian Cabinet decided that Crown Prince
                                    <persName corresp="#p_HIT1">Talal</persName> of Jordan should be
                                proclaimed King the following day upon his arrival in Jordan from
                                Switzerland. On September 6, he took the oath to uphold the
                                Constitution in the presence of both houses of Parliament.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>